Well today was interesting I thought I was so screwed when I got to School and I had to do an AP Chemistry quiz online which I never did anyway, and the AP Statistics worsheet which I never did, and the Taq outline. After school I went home only to go to track at 4:30. Wow was it killer, I heard coach Belle saying that we were gonna go to the weight room so I was excited. Then when we got there it was crazy. I cant feel my legs right now as I type but I guess its all for the greater good. Tommorrow we go to the weightroom for upper body now thats gonna suck but I guess whatever helps me get stronger will work for me.

Until next time Peace to All

Even though most people said PA's test was a complete rape and they wasted their time studying for it I beg to differ. I never studied for it due too a lack of time, if a certain someone does not believe me you may contact Micheal Fernandez and ask him how much I studied for PA's final, and of course I found the test to be rather challenging and it did have many questions which I had never seen before but I feel that if I had studied more I could have done well. As is I'm hoping for a curve to bump me up to a B on the final, which would be excellent, but if that does not happen I think we should get together and complain to the administration. This test of PA's was no where near a fair test and that is why I thk we should complain, I mean almost no one even finished and most people left between 20 and 30 questions blank on the test anyway so all I can say is pray guys pray every night until that progress report comes in. If PA does not curve it may God have pity on our souls and on our Grades.
